    "Earlier work proposing more recent timings, such as 20 ka (ref.",
    "20), could be underestimates stemming from confounding effects of population bottlenecks in cultivated and wild lineages.",
    "The known breeding history of several of our Arabica cultivars provided us with a gold standard set for deducing the Arabica pedigree using Kinship-based INference for Gwas (KING) 59 (Fig. 3).",
